  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tracking Anti-Corruption Summit Commitments</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Business environment, public sector, civil society and the general public.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Anti-Corruption Summit was the first of its kind to place corruption so high on the global agenda but the political will displayed by more than forty governments must be capitalised on and activated early on. This subsequent project will intensify pressure in a subset of countries and on a subset of commitments where substantial gains would directly contribute to the Summit&#x2019;s intention to &#x201C;expose corruption wherever it is found, to pursue and punish those who perpetrate, facilitate or are complicit in it, to support the communities who have suffered from it, and to ensure it does not fester in our government institution, businesses and communities&#x201D;</narrative>
  </description>
